diabetic_retinopathy Stage 3:
In diabetic retinopathy Stage 3, the fundus appearance of the retinal layers may include:
- ILM: irregularities and thickening;
- Nerve Fiber Layer: cotton wool spots and localized swelling;
- Ganglion Cell Layer: loss of ganglion cells, thinning;
- Inner Plexiform Layer: disorganization, potential signal changes;
- Inner Nuclear Layer: microaneurysms, hyperreflective lesions;
- Outer Plexiform Layer: hard exudates, hyperreflective spots;
- Outer Nuclear Layer: potential thinning, irregular reflectivity;
- External Limiting Membrane: disruptions, signal changes;
